Russia President Vladimir Putin said Thursday that Moscow was ready to extend the humanitarian pause in Aleppo, Syria&#8217;s second largest city already badly damaged by bombing, &#8220;as far as possible&#8221;.&#8220;We have made clear our intention to extend as far as possible, depending on the current situation on the ground, the halt in our air strikes,&#8221; Putin said during a press conference broadcast on Russian television following negotiations on Syria with French leader Francois Hollande and German Chancellor Angela Merkel in Berlin.-AFP